=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Guides_Tour_of_UGens_ex2 ===

DESCRIPTION: A dark gritty sound, with fm_or_inharmonic oscillator character around 569 Hz, featuring punchy attack and compressed envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, filtered with resonant_steep_rolloff character, and spectrally sparse.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: punchy
  brightness: dark
  crest_factor_db: compressed
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: gritty
  spectral_complexity_mean: sparse
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 568.9624
  harmonic_decay_rate: -7.2441
  harmonic_regularity: 0.7269
  pitch_clarity: 27.9328
  inharmonicity: 0.3539
  type: fm_or_inharmonic
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -25.2927
  resonance_freq: 1098.1934

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: Tour of UGens Example 2
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Guides/Tour_of_UGens.html
// Tags: Tour_of_UGens, Guides
// ---
// --- Example 2 ---
// parabolic approximation of sine
{ LFPar.ar(LFPar.kr(LFPar.kr(0.2,0,8,10),0, 400,800),0,0.1) }.play;
{ LFPar.ar(LFPar.kr(0.2, 0, 400,800),0,0.1) }.play;
{ LFPar.ar(800,0,0.1) }.play;
// since it is not band limited, there are aliasing artifacts
{ LFPar.ar(XLine.kr(100,15000,6),0,0.1) }.play;
